      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I would advise against overusing lubricating drops, as this can lead to rebound dryness. Instead, try using them as directed and see how your eye responds. As for the antibiotic eye drops, I would exercise caution - they may not be suitable for your current symptoms, and using them without a proper diagnosis can lead to antibiotic resistance. If you're concerned about an infection, I'd recommend waiting until you've tried the lubricating drops and seen a doctor.",
